- The accounting document system of the Social Security sector is currently applied according to Circular No. 178/2012/TT-BTC dated October 23, 2012, of the Minister of Finance, guiding accounting practices applicable to Vietnam Social Security; The State provides guidance on specific indicators for industries and economic sectors to apply them to particular appropriate cases based on these guidelines. Industries and fields may add or omit certain specific indicators suitable for their requirements and the content to be reflected, but must ensure the fundamental elements of the documents and obtain written agreement from the Ministry of Finance. Whether it is a mandatory document or a guiding document, the content of an accounting document must include all the following elements:

+ Name of the document (invoice, receipt voucher, payment voucher...);

+ Document number;

+ Date, month, year of document creation;

+ Name and address of the issuing unit or individual;

+ Content of the arising economic or financial transaction;

+ Quantity, unit price, and amount of the economic or financial transaction recorded in figures; the total amount of the accounting document used for cash receipts or disbursements recorded in figures and in words;

+ Signatures and names of the preparer, approver, and other relevant individuals related to the accounting document.

